title: Dunes
description:
Aeolian Processes on Mars.
Aeolian geology is the study of landforms formed by wind. On Mars, where other processes such as fluvial erosion, volcanism, and tectonism are slow, intermittent, or do not occur in the present era, aeolian activity is the most dynamic geologic process in non-polar areas.
